  "text": "## HTTP Health Check Endpoint Comparison Across Go Projects\n\n### Kubernetes (kubernetes/kubernetes)\n\n**Endpoints:**\n- `/healthz` - Standard health check endpoint\n- `/readyz` - Readiness check endpoint  \n- `/livez` - Liveness check endpoint\n\n**Implementation (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/healthz/healthz.go):**\nKubernetes implements a sophisticated pluggable health check system based on the `HealthChecker` interface. The framework supports:\n\n1. **Built-in Health Checkers:**\n   - `PingHealthz`: Simple always-pass health check\n   - `LogHealthz`: Verifies logging is not blocked (checks klog.Flush)\n   - `NewInformerSyncHealthz`: Validates informer cache synchronization\n   - `NewShutdownHealthz`: Checks if process is shutting down\n   - `NamedCheck/NamedGroupedCheck`: Custom check registration\n\n2. **Installation Functions:**\n   - `InstallHandler()`: Registers handlers on `/healthz` path with optional checks\n   - `InstallReadyzHandler()`: Registers `/readyz` endpoint\n   - `InstallLivezHandler()`: Registers `/livez` endpoint\n   - `InstallPathHandler()`: Generic path registration for custom paths\n\n3. **Usage Pattern:**\n   Components like kubelet (pkg/kubelet/server/server.go), kube-scheduler (cmd/kube-scheduler/app/server.go), and kube-proxy (cmd/kube-proxy/app/server.go) register healthz checks specific to their needs. Kubelet additionally checks syncloop health.\n\n### Grafana (grafana/grafana)\n\n**Endpoints:**\n- `/livez` - Liveness probe endpoint\n- `/readyz` - Readiness probe endpoint\n- `/healthz` - Simple health check endpoint\n- `/api/health` - Detailed health status with database status and version info\n\n**Implementation:**\n\n1. **Probe Endpoints (pkg/server/health.go):**\n   - `HealthNotifier`: Thread-safe mechanism for signaling readiness state using atomic.Bool\n   - `LivezHandler()`: Always returns 200 OK (process is alive)\n   - `ReadyzHandler()`: Returns 200 OK if ready, 503 Service Unavailable if not ready\n   - `RegisterHealthEndpoints()`: Registers both /livez and /readyz on a mux.Router\n\n2. **HTTP Server Health Handlers (pkg/api/http_server.go):**\n   - `healthzHandler()`: Simple middleware that returns 200 OK if Grafana server is running (GET/HEAD on /healthz)\n   - `apiHealthHandler()`: JSON-based health response that checks database connectivity:\n     * Returns database status (\"ok\" or \"failing\")\n     * Returns HTTP 503 if database is unhealthy\n     * Includes version info (BuildVersion, BuildCommit, EnterpriseBuildCommit) when not hidden\n     * Performs `databaseHealthy()` check to validate DB connection\n\n3. **Purpose:**\n   - `/livez` and `/readyz`: Kubernetes-compatible probe endpoints\n   - `/healthz`: Simple health indicator for basic monitoring\n   - `/api/health`: Detailed health information including dependency (database) status\n\n### Prometheus (prometheus/prometheus)\n\n**Endpoints:**\n- `/-/healthy` - Health status endpoint\n- `/-/ready` - Readiness status endpoint\n\n**Implementation (web/web.go):**\n\n1. **State Management:**\n   - `ReadyStatus` enum with three states:\n     * `NotReady` (0): Server is starting up\n     * `Ready` (1): Server is ready to serve requests\n     * `Stopping` (2): Server is shutting down\n   - `Handler.ready`: Atomic uint32 field storing current ready status\n   - `SetReady()`: Updates ready status and metrics\n\n2. **Health Endpoints:**\n   - `/-/healthy` (GET/HEAD): Always returns 200 OK with message \"%s is Healthy.\\n\"\n   - `/-/ready` (GET/HEAD): Wrapped with `testReady()` middleware\n\n3. **Readiness Check (testReady function):**\n   - Returns 200 OK if `Ready` status\n   - Returns 503 Service Unavailable if `NotReady` or `Stopping` status\n   - Sets `X-Prometheus-Stopping` header to \"true\" when shutting down, \"false\" otherwise\n   - Used as middleware wrapper for routes that should only work when server is ready (e.g., `/federate`, `/consoles`)\n\n4. **Usage (cmd/prometheus/main.go):**\n   - `SetReady(NotReady)` during initialization\n   - `SetReady(Ready)` after database loading and scrape manager startup\n   - `SetReady(Stopping)` when shutdown signal received\n\n### Key Differences\n\n| Aspect | Kubernetes | Grafana | Prometheus |\n|--------|-----------|---------|------------|\n| **Health Check Model** | Pluggable checkers framework | State-based readiness + DB check | State-based readiness |\n| **Endpoints** | /healthz, /readyz, /livez | /livez, /readyz, /healthz, /api/health | /-/healthy, /-/ready |\n| **Database Check** | Via informer sync | Via databaseHealthy() function | N/A |\n| **Custom Checks** | Yes (HealthChecker interface) | Limited (HealthNotifier state) | No |\n| **Response Format** | Plain text | JSON for /api/health, text otherwise | Plain text |\n| **Version Info** | N/A | Conditional in /api/health | N/A |\n| **Stopping State** | Via NewShutdownHealthz | N/A | Explicit Stopping state |\n"
}

